-- Invesco Perpetual Names Mustoe as Investment Officer; Yerbury Steps Down
-- Gavin Finch
-- 2010-04-27T10:45:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/invesco-perpetual-names-mustoe-as-investment-officer-yerbury-steps-down.html

          
          
             Invesco Perpetual, the U.K. money
manager, hired Nick Mustoe as chief investment officer,
replacing Bob Yerbury.  
 Mustoe, 49, was previously chief investment officer at
Pictet Asset Management Ltd., where he was responsible for the
equity investment teams, the company said in an e-mailed
statement today. Mustoe will report to James Robertson, chief
executive officer of Invesco Perpetual, which is based in
Henley-on-Thames, England.  
 “Nick’s wealth of experience and expertise will add
further depth to our world-class investment team,” Robertson
said in the statement.  
 Yerbury remains a senior managing director at Invesco Ltd.
and part of the Inveso Perpetual management team.  
